Durban - Police have confirmed two alleged hijackers are due to appear in the Durban Magistrate's Court soon. In the first incident Point SAPS officers arrested a suspect hours after he allegedly hijacked a vehicle in the Durban CBD on Monday. According to police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, the man, 29, had been trying to kick-start the vehicle in Mayville when police pounced on him. In the second incident, on Monday evening, a man was in his vehicle at Umbilo when he was approached by a group of men who threatened him with a firearm and robbed him of his vehicle. "The suspects failed to drive the vehicle and stole the victims cellphone before they fled the scene in their getaway vehicle." Zwane said Umbilo SAPS were alerted and a description of the getaway vehicle was circulated to all police officers on duty. "Umbilo police officers spotted the getaway vehicle in their policing precinct." A 36-year-old suspect was arrested and Zwane said more arrests are imminent. POST 